  "prompt": "Someone deleted me on snapchat, so I deleted him & now he appears in my Added me section, but I cannot see his score. Does this mean he added me back?",
  "response": "If someone deleted you on Snapchat and you subsequently deleted them, but now they appear in your \"Added Me\" section without a visible Snapchat score, it typically means they have added you back. Here\u2019s why this happens:\n\n1. **Added Me Section**: When someone sends you a friend request or adds you back after you\u2019ve deleted them, they will show up in the \"Added Me\" section of your Snapchat app.\n\n2. **No Visible Snapchat Score**: If you can\u2019t see their Snap score, it usually indicates that they haven\u2019t re-added you as a friend yet or they have restrictive privacy settings. However, if they\u2019re in your \"Added Me\" section, it\u2019s more likely they\u2019ve sent you a friend request or added you back but you haven\u2019t reciprocated yet.\n\n3. **Next Steps**: If you see them in the \"Added Me\" section, you can choose to add them back by tapping the \u201c+\u201d button next to their name. Once you add them back, their Snapchat score should become visible again, assuming their privacy settings allow it.\n\nIn summary, their presence in the \"Added Me\" section suggests they\u2019ve initiated some form of reconnection, but you\u2019ll need to add them back to fully restore the friendship and see their Snapchat score.",
